<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=711&amp;p=6141#p6141</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=711&amp;p=6141#p6141"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[&quot;Bugs&quot; due to pressing left+right]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=711&amp;p=6141#p6141"><![CDATA[
Heh, if you press left and right at the same moment, it will choose the opposite direction as was last used for that axis. So repeating left+right, release, left+right, release, etc. will give alternating directions for the X axis.<br /><br />Be sure to provide a way to disable it so people wanting to intentionally invoke these behaviors (as are possible on a real NES) won't be foiled. Setting the mask to ~0 will conveniently disable the filtering.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Tue Nov 01, 2005 5:17 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
